headline: A Look at International Paper's Valuation Following Georgia Mill Closures and Slumping Packaging Demand
summary: When a company as established as International Paper (NYSE:IP) makes a move like closing two of its Georgia mills, investors and industry watchers alike take notice. This decision comes on the back of a sharp downturn in demand for corrugated packaging, which has now dropped to lows not seen since 2016. With about 9% of U.S. containerboard capacity coming off the market, the company is clearly responding to real shifts in industry demand and broader economic pressures. This shakeup is not...
